    Node: Get Negative Transform

Input parameter.VariableNode_9.Value
    Node: Setup Arm

Setting initial positions on the IK and FK arm controls.

Args
::Bones:: Arm Bones, e.g. Upperarm, LowerArm, Hand
::FK Space:: UpperArm FK Space
::FK Controls:: Array of FK Arm Controls
::IK Controls:: IK Hand Control
::Pole Vector Control:: Arm Pole Vector Control
::Fingers Space:: Finger Space Null
::IK Parents:: What the IK Control and Pole Vector will be parented to. 
::Negative Side:: Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the    Left side will be False, Right Side will be True   (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Parenting IK Control and PV Control under the IK Parents Array (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Setup Leg

Setting initial positions on the IK and FK leg controls, pole vector controls and thigh space

Args
::Bones:: Leg Bones (thigh, calf and foot)
::FK Space:: Thigh FK Control Space Null
::FK Controls:: Leg FK Controls
::IK Control:: Leg IK Control (foot ik control)
::Pole Vector Control:: Leg Pole Vector Control
::IK Parents:: What the IK Control and Pole Vector will be parented to.
::Negative Side:: Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the    Left side will be False, Right Side will be True.  
::Pole Vector Null:: Leg pole vector footFollow Null (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Setting Transform Array Values (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: X Scale Value is -1 if Negative Side Bool is True, and 1 if False (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Parenting IK Control and PV Control under the IK Parents Array (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Setup Foot

Setting initial positions on the ball IK and FK controls, and toe space position

Args
::Bone:: Ball Bone
::FK Control:: Ball FK Control
::IK Control:: Ball IK Control
::Pole Vector Control:: Leg Pole Vector Control
::Toe Space:: Null Toe Space
::Negative Side:: Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the    Left side will be False, Right Side will be True.   (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Scale X value is -1 if Negative Side bool is True, and 1 if False (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Scale X value is -1 if Negative Side bool is True, and 1 if False (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: adds 90 in the Rotation Y value if Negative Side bool is False (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: adds and additional 180 in the Rotation Y value if Negative Side bool is True (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Setting IK Mode from IKFK Switch (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Forward Arm

Sets IK and FK Control visibility,  matches IK and FK controls, and Auto Keys when switching between IK and FK. Connects IK and FK arm controls to the arm bones. Sets the updated Finger space. 

Args
::FK Controls:: Arm FK Controls
::IK Control:: Hand IK Control
::IK Effector:: Hand IK Control
::Pole Vector Control:: Arm PV Control
::IKFK Switch Control:: Arm FK IK Switch Control
::FK Orient Control:: Arm FK local Control
::Arm Space:: Null upper fk ctrl space
::FK Orient References:: Clavicle and Body Control
::Finger Space:: Null finger space
::Bones:: Arm Bones
::Softness:: Hand IK Ctrl Softness Animation Channel
::Enable Stretch:: Hand IK Stretch Animation Channel
::Previous IK Mode:: Arm IK Mode Bool set by arm fkik switch Animation Channel
::Negative Side::Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the Left side will be False, Right Side will be True  
::IK Orient Null:: Null hand ikOrient
::IK Orient Control:: Hand IKorient Control
:: IK Orient:: Hand IK Ctrl Animation Channel Keep Aligned
::Previous Align:: Arm IK Align set by Hand IK Ctrl Keep Align Animation channel (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Forward Leg

Sets IK and FK Control visibility and matches IK and FK controls,when switching between IK and FK. Connects IK and FK leg controls to the leg bones.

Args
::FK Controls:: Leg FK Controls
::IK Control:: Foot IK Control
::IK Effector:: Foot IK Null
::Pole Vector Control:: Leg PV Control
::IKFK Switch Control:: Leg FK IK Switch Control
::Bones:: Leg Bones
::Softness:: Leg IK Ctrl Animation Channel Softness
::Enable Stretch:: Leg IK Animation Channel Stretch
::Previous IK Mode:: Leg IK Mode Bool set by Leg fkik switch Animation Channel
::Negative Side::Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the Left side will be False, Right Side will be True  
::Pole Vector Null:: Leg pv footFollow Null (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Set IK Mode from IKFK Switch (EdGraphNode_Comment)
  Graph: Forward Foot

    Node: Backward Arm

    Node: Setup Reverse Foot

Setting initial positions of the foot roll controls, BK Controls, BK Buffer, and roll Buffer

Args
::BK Buffers:: heel control
::BK Controls:: heel control, tip control, foot_bk control, foot ik Null
::Bones:: heel, tip, ball and foot bones.
::Roll Control:: Foot roll Control
::Roll Buffer:: Null foot roll bfr
::Negative Side:: Boolean. Checks if its building the Default or Negated axis. In this case the    Left side will be False, Right Side will be True.   (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Set BK Buffers and BK Controls (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: If Get Bones is positive (left side) set the corresponding BK Buffer and BK Controls transform with the translation and scale of the Bone given (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: The rotations of the BK Controls will be set from the heel rotation (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: If Get Bones is negative (right side) the Rotation X vvalue will have 180 added to it, and -1 set for the Scale X value for the corresponding BK Buffer and BK Controls translation and scale. (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Set Roll Buffer and Roll Control (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Set the Roll Buffer and Roll Control initial translation from the last element in the Bones array (foot joint). The rotation is the Heel_Rotation value. If it is negative (right side) the Scale X value is set to -1 (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Forward Reverse Foot

Connect Reverse Foot Controls to Reverse Foot Bones. Setting BK and Roll Control visbility. 

Args
::BK Buffers:: Null heel, null tip, null foot BK
::BK Controls:: Heel, tip and foot bk controls
::Roll Control:: foot roll control
::Roll Buffer:: Null foot roll bfr
::IKFK Switch Control:: Leg FK IK Switch Control
::Roll Clamp:: Float to clamp the Roll.
::Roll Blend:: roll blend control animation float channel Float Value (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Set IK Mode from IKFK switch (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Roll Buffer Rotation (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Set IK Mode based on IKFK Switch (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Forward Spine

Updates the IK and FK Spine Control Visibility. Sets Pelvis Bone Transform. Connects Ik and FK controls to Spine Bones. Keys Controls.

Args
::FK Controls:: FK Spine Controls
::IK Controls:: IK Spine Controls
::Bones:: Spine Bones
::Pelvis Bone:: Pelvis Bone
::Chest Space:: Null Chest Space
::IKFK Switch Control:: Spine IKFK switch Control
::Enable Stretch:: Chest Control Bool Channel Spine Stretch Switch
::Spline Offsets:: Transform array set in Setup Spine Function
:Default Length:: Float set in Setup Spine Function. Used for IK Spline.
::Previous IK Mode:: Global Ctrl Bool Channel Spine FKIK switch. (EdGraphNode_Comment)

Input parameter.VariableNode_12_2.Value
    Node: Forward Neck

Updates the IK and FK neck and head Control Visibility. Updates Head IK and FK Space. Connects Ik and FK controls to Neck and Head Bones. Keys Controls.

Args
::FK Controls:: FK Neck and Head Controls
::IK Control:: IK Head Control
::Bones:: Neck and Head Bones
::Head Orient Control:: Head Local Control animation channel
::IKFK Switch Control:: Spine IKFK switch Control
::Mid IK Null:: Null Head Mid
::Head FK Space:: Null head fk space
::Head IK Space:: Null head ik space
::Head Orient Reference:: Body Control
::Length:: Neck Length Set up in the Setup Neck function. Used for IK Spline.
::Enable Stretch:: Head Control Bool Channel Stretch
::Previous IK Mode:: Global Ctrl Bool Channel Neck FKIK switch (EdGraphNode_Comment)
    Node: Set IK Mode based on IKFK switch. Local Space Set on Head Orient Control (EdGraphNode_Comment)
  Graph: Spine Match IK onto FK

    Node: Forward SNC

Connects Simplified Neck Control (SNC) to Neck and Head Bones.

Args
::SNC Control:: Simplified Neck Control
::SNC Control Group:: Offset (Null) Group For Head SNC Control
::SNC Drivers:: Driver Nodes (Controls) For Basic Bend and Twist Setup
::Neck 01 Driver Bend Fwd:: Bend Fwd Multiplier Used for Basic Bend and Twist Setup
::Neck 01 Driver Bend Back:: Bend Back Multiplier Used for Basic Bend and Twist Setup
::Neck 01 Driver Bend Left-Right:: Bend Left and Right Multiplier Used for Basic Bend and Twist Setup
::Neck 01 Driver Twist Left-Right:: Twist Laft and Right Multiplier Used for Basic Bend and Twist Setup
::Spline IK Handles:: Nodes (Controls) used as IK Spoline Drivers 
::Spline IK Bones:: Additional Neck Chain Driven by IK Spline
::Deformation Bones:: Neck and Head Bones (EdGraphNode_Comment)

    Node: Spline IK
Variable spline rig for spines, tails, and dangles.

Requires a minimum of 4 inputs (controls and joints). 

Args
::Controls:: Controls corresponding to the spline cv points. (Minimum of 4)
::Bones:: The bone hierarchy that attaches to the spline. (Minimum of 4)
::Debug:: Draw the splines.
::Stretch:: Allow the bones to stretch along the spline.
::Secondary Spline Direction:: Where to draw the second spline that is used for twist. This will vary based on the rig. Best used with debug = True.
::Spline Mode:: Choose type of curve to make.
::Samples Per Segment:: Number of samples (EdGraphNode_Comment)
